<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc9e7ddcd-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s485h–2"><num value="485h–2">§ 485h–2.</num><heading> Amendments to existing contracts</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary is authorized to negotiate amendments to existing contracts entered into pursuant to subsection (e) of <ref href="/us/usc/t43/s485h">section 485h of this title</ref> to conform said contracts to the provisions of sections 485h–1 to 485h–5 of this title.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc9e7ddce-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/act/1956-07-02/ch492/s2">July 2, 1956, ch. 492, § 2</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/70/484">70 Stat. 484</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idc9e7ddcf-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idc9e7ddd0-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="idc9e7ddd1-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was not enacted as part of the Reclamation Project Act of 1939 which comprises this subchapter.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
